{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0eba90c-f7bc-40e8-a721-e81b72bbf559","content":"\n\nHere's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n- `--filter` is bridged through `dotnet test` and still works as-is.\n- Everything after `--` is passed to the new platform runner.\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` / `--blame-hang-timeout` → `--hangdump` / `--hangdump-timeout`\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n| Old (VSTest) | New (Testing.Platform) |\n|---|---|\n| *(built-in)* | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| *(built-in)* | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| *(built-in)* | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\nAlso ensure `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` and `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` are set in your test `.csproj`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"34bf49ee-66a5-4099-870f-384d1410c089","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a code change request.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n- Filter syntax changes from `--filter` to `--filter` (mostly compatible) or `--test-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- Code coverage with `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` becomes `--coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage\n\n\n- Blame-related flags like `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` map to `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` respectively, with timeout options adjusting similarly\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8, `dotnet test` still works as the entry point, but arguments are passed through to the test host differently—some flags remain compatible while others need to be remapped to the new platform's naming conventions.\n\nLooking at the specific command-line mappings: filters work through `dotnet test` or via native runner syntax, logging requires the TrxReport extension, code coverage uses the new `--coverage` flags with the CodeCoverage package, and crash/hang diagnostics depend on their respective extensions being installed. I need to clarify how the bridging works between `dotnet test` and Microsoft.Testing.Platform—some arguments like `--filter` are passed through, but others need the `--` separator. The native platform uses `--treenode-filter` for filtering, and I should list out the specific NuGet packages required for each feature: TrxReport for test results, CodeCoverage for coverage metrics, CrashDump for crash diagnostics, and HangDump for hang detection.","outputTokens":1293},"id":"6e30c601-0041-48b3-886b-4a575646d92f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:49:21.992Z","parentId":"4b3a53d0-426a-4069-8490-584002c2aa62"}
